\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs the Department's KPI framework at the scorecard and governance level.
 It defines what qualifies as a KPI,
 the required domains of KPI coverage,
 the recordkeeping and review cadence,
 and the routing rules for performance results that require action.
 Operational data collection remains governed by the source policies identified in the KPI register;
 corrective action follows the lifecycle defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 and improvement intake follows the routing defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.16"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 KPI Qualification Criteria
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A measure shall qualify as a KPI under this policy only when it meets all of the following conditions:
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
It is reviewed at the IT Director or Assistant IT Director quarterly governance level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
It reflects departmental outcome,
 control health,
 or operational resilience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
It is stable enough to trend across review periods.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
It is capable of triggering a governance response.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Measures that do not meet this threshold remain supporting metrics owned by their source policies.
\end_layout

