\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 KPI Register and Definition Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a live KPI register in the System of Engagement.
 The KPI register is the authoritative operational catalog for KPI definitions and current status.
 The policy manual defines governance requirements;
 the KPI register carries current formulas,
 targets,
 and statuses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Each KPI record in the register shall include,
 at minimum:
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
KPI title.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Assigned domain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Source policy or source system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Calculation method or formula.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Review cadence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Target value.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Warning threshold,
 where used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Critical threshold,
 where used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Trend direction convention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Expected routing action when performance falls outside approved tolerances.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Approving authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Approval date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Effective date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Retired date,
 where applicable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
