\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Underperformance Thresholds and Routing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Single-Period Miss
\series default
:
 A KPI single-period miss exists when a KPI falls below its approved target or outside its approved tolerance during one quarterly review period.
 The Assistant IT Director shall document a single-period miss in the Quarterly KPI Review Summary and shall monitor it during the next review cycle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Underperformance Pattern
\series default
:
 A KPI underperformance pattern exists when either:
 (a) the same KPI records two consecutive quarterly misses;
 or (b) the IT Director determines that a single deviation is sufficiently severe,
 persistent,
 or strategically significant to require tracked improvement despite the absence of a second consecutive miss.
 Where the IT Director invokes (b),
 the IT Director shall document the determination in the Quarterly KPI Review Summary,
 including the affected KPI,
 the affected service or control domain,
 the operational impact,
 any security or compliance impact,
 and the reason immediate tracked improvement is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Routing
\series default
:
 Upon identification of a KPI underperformance pattern,
 the Assistant IT Director shall log a Service Improvement Register entry in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.16"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 unless the issue instead requires direct routing into the Corrective Action Plan lifecycle under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Where KPI deviation reflects a control deficiency,
 compliance gap,
 sustained policy nonconformance,
 or other condition requiring formal remediation with milestones,
 the Assistant IT Director shall initiate or update a Corrective Action Plan in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This policy does not create a separate remediation tracker.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Pattern Analysis
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall review Recurring Ticket Ratio and similar pattern-based KPIs for evidence of documentation weakness,
 training need,
 recurring failure mode,
 or process design deficiency.
 Where the analysis identifies a systemic improvement opportunity,
 the Assistant IT Director shall route the issue through the Service Improvement Register.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Organizational Health Boundary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Organizational Health KPIs shall be limited to indicators that affect workforce sustainability,
 delivery capacity,
 succession fragility,
 or operational overdependence on specific personnel.
 The Assistant IT Director shall present Organizational Health KPIs in aggregate within the Quarterly KPI Review Summary.
 KPI governance records shall not include named employee performance ratings,
 disciplinary facts,
 medical information,
 or HR-confidential details.
 This policy is not an employee ranking or disciplinary scorecard.
 The IT Director shall route any individual personnel action arising from organizational health review through normal supervisory and HR processes,
 not through the KPI governance process defined in this policy.
\end_layout

